Sentencas: Symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) that feature nanostructured SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-delta (SFMO) electrodes which are impregnated into porous La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) skeletons by solution infiltration technique are prepared.
Titulo: Characterization of symmetrical SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ electrodes in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The symmetrical SOFCs are investigated in detail by operating with 5 wt% Fe-loaded activated carbon as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: Characterization of symmetrical SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ electrodes in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A typical single cell can give a maximum power density of 405 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, which is comparable to the results with Ni-based anode-supported SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of symmetrical SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ electrodes in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Also, the direct carbon SOFC (DC-SOFC) with reloaded fuel can recover to its initial performance.
Titulo: Characterization of symmetrical SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ electrodes in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The microstructures and XRD of the electrodes after test are also examined and analysed.
Titulo: Characterization of symmetrical SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ electrodes in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results show that the SFMO-LSGM composite anode remains porous and maintains its structure stability, implying that the symmetrical SFMO electrodes can be applied into DC-SOFCs.
Titulo: Characterization of symmetrical SrFe0.75Mo0.25O3-δ electrodes in direct carbon solid oxide fuel cells
